    <item>
      <title>Using VMware.Sdk.Vsphere: Commands for vSphere</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/post/vcf-90/vcf-90-powercli-vsphere-cmdlets/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 22 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/post/vcf-90/vcf-90-powercli-vsphere-cmdlets/</guid>
      <description>
        
          
            &lt;p&gt;VCF PowerCLI 9.0 now includes a module called &lt;code&gt;VMware.Sdk.Vsphere&lt;/code&gt;, this modules contains auto-generated cmdlets to support vSphere Public APIs. Use can use this post as a quick reference guide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;connecting-to-a-vcenter-instance-with-local-credentials&#34;&gt;Connecting to a vCenter Instance with Local Credentials&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start a PowerShell session.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Connect to a vCenter instance using local credentials by running the following command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;Connect-VIServer&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-Server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;sfo-m01&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-vc01&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;py&#34;&gt;sfo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;py&#34;&gt;rainpole&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;py&#34;&gt;io&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-Username&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;administrator&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;@vsphere&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;py&#34;&gt;local&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-Password&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;VMw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;@re1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;VMw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;@re1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Once connected the following information is stored in &lt;code&gt;$global:DefaultVIServer&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;Name    : sfo-m01-vc01.sfo.rainpole.io
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;Port    : &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;443&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;User    VSPHERE.LOCAL&lt;span class=&#34;se&#34;&gt;\A&lt;/span&gt;dministrator
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;4&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Disconnect from a vCenter instance by running the following command:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;Disconnect-VIServer&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-Server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;sfo-m01&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-vc01&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;py&#34;&gt;sfo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;py&#34;&gt;rainpole&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;py&#34;&gt;io&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NOTE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
          
          
        
